---
/**
 * Privacy policy, live, customer-facing.
 *
 * Source of truth for the policy text. The markdown draft at
 * clients/android/privacy-policy.md predates this page and is now a
 * historical reference; if you update the policy, update THIS file.
 *
 * Linked from:
 *   - Google Play store listing ("Privacy policy URL")
 *   - the Lattice VPN Android app (Settings → About)
 *   - the website Footer component
 *   - Stripe customer-facing emails (footer)
 *
 * Any time you change material policy text (what data we collect, how
 * long we retain it, who we share it with, governing law) you MUST
 * bump the EFFECTIVE_DATE constant. That's the customer's signal
 * that the policy changed under them.
 */
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';

const EFFECTIVE_DATE   = '2026-05-26';
const LEGAL_ENTITY     = 'KRYPTOKNIGHTZ LLC';
const REGISTERED_ADDR  = '87-154a Maipalaoa Road, Waianae, HI 96792, USA';
const GOVERNING_LAW    = 'the State of Hawaii, United States of America';
const LEGAL_EMAIL      = 'legal@latticevpn.ai';
const SUPPORT_EMAIL    = 'support@latticevpn.ai';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="Lattice VPN's privacy policy. No logs, no accounts, no tracking. Here's exactly what we do and don't collect."
>
  <article class="pt-32 pb-20 mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
    <header class="text-center mb-12">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-slate-100 border border-slate-200 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-slate-600 mb-6">
        PRIVACY POLICY
      </span>
      <h1 class="font-display font-extrabold text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-3">
        Privacy policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-mono">
        Effective {EFFECTIVE_DATE} · Applies to the Lattice VPN Android application
        (<code>ai.latticevpn.android</code>) and the Lattice VPN service.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-mono mt-1">
        Provider: {LEGAL_ENTITY} ("Lattice", "we", "us") · Contact: <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL_EMAIL}`} class="text-mint-700 underline">{LEGAL_EMAIL}</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <section class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-7 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Summary</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Lattice VPN is a no-logs VPN. We do not record what you do online.
        We collect the minimum needed to connect your device to a VPN
        server, and nothing that would let us, or anyone else,
        reconstruct your browsing. We do not sell or rent data to anyone,
        and the app contains no advertising or analytics trackers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- What we don't collect -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">What we do NOT collect</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        We do not log, store, or monitor:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-2 list-disc pl-6">
        <li>the websites, apps, or services you connect to;</li>
        <li>your DNS queries;</li>
        <li>your traffic content, or traffic metadata such as timestamps and bandwidth tied to your identity;</li>
        <li>a history of when you connected or disconnected;</li>
        <li>your originating IP address in association with your activity.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">
        Our VPN servers run in volatile memory (RAM). They are not configured to write traffic or connection logs to disk.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- What we process -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">What we process to provide the service</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        To create and route your encrypted tunnel, the app and servers
        handle the following, kept to the minimum and not linked to your
        real-world identity:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-3 list-disc pl-6">
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">Provisioning data.</strong> When you
          select a location, the app contacts our provisioning API and
          registers your device as a VPN peer. This request includes the
          public keys your device generates locally (its WireGuard public
          key and its Rosenpass post-quantum public key) and the account
          number you entered when you subscribed. It does <strong>not</strong>
          include your name, email address, or phone number. The
          corresponding private keys are generated on your device and
          never leave it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">Account number.</strong> When you
          subscribe on latticevpn.ai, we generate a random account number
          that you enter into the app. This is the only credential the
          VPN service knows about you. It is not derived from any
          personal information.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">Routing state.</strong> While you
          are connected, the server holds your assigned internal VPN IP
          address and your public key in memory so it can route packets.
          This is operational state, not a log, and is not retained as a
          record of your activity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">Network-level IP address.</strong> As
          with any internet connection, our server necessarily receives
          the IP address your device connects from in order to establish
          the tunnel. We do not store it as part of an activity log.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">Local app data.</strong> Your
          selected region and your VPN configuration are stored on your
          device so the app works between launches. This data stays on
          your device.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Third parties -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Third-party services</h2>
      <ul class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-3 list-disc pl-6">
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">IP address display.</strong> To
          show you your current IP address inside the app, the app makes
          a request to a third-party IP-lookup service
          (<code>ipify.org</code>). That service receives the IP address
          of the request. No other personal information is sent to it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">No analytics or advertising.</strong>
          The app integrates no analytics, advertising, attribution, or
          third-party crash-reporting SDKs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="font-semibold">Payments.</strong> Subscriptions
          are purchased on our website (<code>latticevpn.ai</code>),
          where payments are processed by Stripe, Inc. Stripe handles
          your payment details under its own privacy policy; we do not
          receive or store full payment card numbers. No payment is
          taken inside the Android app.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Data sharing -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Data sharing and legal requests</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        We do not sell, rent, or trade personal data. Because we do not
        keep activity logs, we have nothing to disclose that would
        reveal what a user did online. If we receive a legally binding
        request, we can only provide the limited information we
        actually hold, which does not include browsing or connection
        history.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Retention -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Data retention</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Operational state (such as routing state) exists only for the
        life of your connection and is held in server memory; it is
        cleared when you disconnect.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        <strong class="font-semibold">Device records.</strong>
        Provisioning records (the per-device public keys and assigned
        tunnel IP that let our servers route your traffic) are kept
        while your subscription is active. When the device-per-account
        limit is reached, the least-recently-seen device record is
        automatically evicted to make room for the new one. When a
        subscription ends, the associated device records are no longer
        usable for new connections.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="font-semibold">Billing records.</strong> Records
        associated with your Stripe subscription (account number,
        subscription dates, payment confirmations, never your card
        details, which Stripe holds) are retained for the lifetime of
        the subscription and for a period required by United States tax
        and accounting law (typically seven years) thereafter, after
        which they are deleted.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Security -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Security</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Traffic between your device and our servers is encrypted with
        WireGuard and additionally protected by Rosenpass post-quantum
        key exchange, which refreshes the tunnel's pre-shared key every
        few minutes. No method of transmission or storage is perfectly
        secure, but we design the service to minimize the data that
        exists to be exposed in the first place.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Children -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Children</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Lattice VPN is not directed at children and is intended for
        users aged 18 and over. We do not knowingly collect personal
        information from children.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Rights -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Your rights</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access,
        correct, or delete personal data we hold about you, or to
        object to certain processing. Because we intentionally hold very
        little data, some requests may have little to act on. To make a
        request, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL_EMAIL}`} class="text-mint-700 underline">{LEGAL_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Changes -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes
        will be posted at this URL with an updated effective date.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-7">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-slate-900 mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Questions about this policy or your privacy:
        <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL_EMAIL}`} class="text-mint-700 underline">{LEGAL_EMAIL}</a>
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        General support:
        <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`} class="text-mint-700 underline">{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-mono">
        {LEGAL_ENTITY}<br/>
        {REGISTERED_ADDR}<br/>
        Governing law: {GOVERNING_LAW}
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
